<sect1 id="index_1intro">
<title>Introduction</title>
<para>ESP Menu is a customizable menu system for ESP32 microcontrollers with SSD1306 OLED displays and rotary encoder input. It provides a flexible and extensible menu creation framework for ESP32-based projects using a JSON-based configuration system.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="index_1features">
<title>Key Features</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>SSD1306 OLED Display Support</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Rotary Encoder Input (up to 4 encoders)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>LVGL Integration</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>JSON-based Menu Definition</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Template-based Code Generation</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>NVS Support for storing parameters</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Component-based Architecture</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
